to RAB's collection efforts.16 RAB maintains that the entry of
this ‘surprise’ evidence was an attempt by Radbil to deprive
it of its ability to defend itself on the issue of whether Plaintiff
had incurred damages due to counseling efforts.
*3  Third, RAB claims that Radbill made an untimely
