Countercls. ¶ 45.
Underwriters did not mention its request for, or Defendants'
counterclaim for, declaratory judgment in its motion
for summary judgment. But “district courts are widely
acknowledged to possess the power to enter summary
judgments sua sponte , so long as the losing party was on
notice that [it] had to come forward with all of [its] evidence.”
Celotex Corp. v. Catrett, 477 U.S. 317, 326 (1986).
